<p>The University of British Columbia and the city of Vancouver are on the traditional, ancestral, and unceded territory of the Coast Salish Peoples.  Specifically the xÊ·mÉ™Î¸kÊ·É™yÌ“É™m (Musqueam), É™lÌ“ilwÉ™taÉÉ¬ (Tsleil-Waututh), and SkwxwÃº7mesh-ulh (Squamish) Nations.  There are nearly 200 First Nations spread through BC, and many more across the continent.</p>

